{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Y3xoGvFKwwMoz11GENWTqX","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the frontend structure. Let me compile my findings:\n\n## Frontend Exploration Report: Polez GUI\n\nI've thoroughly explored the `/Users/captain/code/github.com/polez/gui/src` directory. Here's a comprehensive analysis:\n\n### 1. **Main React Components and Structure**\n\nThe application follows a clear hierarchical structure:\n\n**Entry Point:**\n- `/Users/captain/code/github.com/polez/gui/src/main.tsx` - Creates React root and renders App\n\n**Root App Component:**\n- `/Users/captain/code/github.com/polez/gui/src/App.tsx` - Main application shell that orchestrates all components:\n  - Manages `fileInfo` state (passed to FileHeader and consumed by child components)\n  - Renders layout with 5 major sections in sequence:\n    1. FileHeader (file upload/info)\n    2. Waveform visualization\n    3. Spectrogram visualization\n    4. 2-column grid: DetectionPanel + BitPlaneViewer\n    5. CleanPanel (sanitization)\n\n**Component Breakdown:**\n\n| Component | File | Purpose |\n|-----------|------|---------|\n| FileHeader | `/Users/captain/code/github.com/polez/gui/src/components/FileHeader.tsx` | File upload with drag-drop, progress tracking, displays loaded file metadata (format, sample rate, channels, duration) |\n| Waveform | `/Users/captain/code/github.com/polez/gui/src/components/Waveform.tsx` | Interactive waveform visualization using WaveSurfer.js library with play/pause/stop controls |\n| Spectrogram | `/Users/captain/code/github.com/polez/gui/src/components/Spectrogram.tsx` | Canvas-based spectrogram visualization with adjustable frequency range (8-24 kHz) and color mapping |\n| DetectionPanel | `/Users/captain/code/github.com/polez/gui/src/components/DetectionPanel.tsx` | Detection analysis UI with confidence bars for watermark, AI watermark, statistical, and metadata detection |\n| BitPlaneViewer | `/Users/captain/code/github.com/polez/gui/src/components/BitPlaneViewer.tsx` | Bit-plane bias analysis showing 8 planes (LSB-MSB) with bias detection highlighting |\n| CleanPanel | `/Users/captain/code/github.com/polez/gui/src/components/CleanPanel.tsx` | **Core clean operation UI** - mode selection, triggering cleaning, results display, and file save |\n\n### 2. **How Clean Endpoint Response is Handled/Displayed**\n\nThe `CleanPanel` component handles the clean endpoint response completely:\n\n**Response Type (`CleanResponse` interface):**\n```typescript\n{\n  success: boolean;\n  metadata_removed: number;\n  patterns_found: number;\n  patterns_suppressed: number;\n  quality_loss: number;\n  processing_time: number;\n  before: any;        // Detection analysis before cleaning\n  after: any;         // Detection analysis after cleaning\n}\n```\n\n**Handling Flow:**\n1. User selects mode (Fast/Standard/Preserving/Aggressive) via dropdown\n2. Clicks \"Clean\" button → calls `cleanFile(mode)` via `/api/clean` POST\n3. Sets `result` state with response\n4. **Display shows:**\n   - Quick stats row: Quality loss %, processing time, metadata count, patterns found/suppressed\n   - Side-by-side comparison with `DetectionColumn` component showing before/after detection results\n   - A \"Save File\" button appears after successful clean\n\n**Quality Metrics Displayed:**\n- Quality loss percentage\n- Processing time in seconds\n- Metadata removed count\n- Pattern statistics (found vs suppressed)\n\n### 3. **Verification and Quality Score UI**\n\nThe quality verification is **implicit rather than explicit** - it leverages the before/after detection comparison:\n\n**Quality Verification Method:**\n- `DetectionColumn` component renders before/after detection data side-by-side\n- Shows watermark confidence bars (before vs after) - visual comparison indicates cleaning effectiveness\n- Shows AI watermark detection (before vs after)\n- Shows statistical AI probability (before vs after)\n- Shows metadata tag counts (before vs after)\n- Quality loss percentage explicitly displayed as a metric\n\n**Confidence Bar Component:**\n- Reusable `ConfidenceBar` component shows percentage value with color coding:\n  - Red (>70%): High confidence\n  - Yellow (40-70%): Medium confidence\n  - Green (<40%): Low confidence\n- Used in both DetectionPanel and CleanPanel for consistent scoring display\n\n### 4. **Complete Component Hierarchy**\n\n```\nApp.tsx\n├── FileHeader\n│   └── File upload UI with drag-drop, progress bar\n│\n├── Waveform\n│   └── WaveSurfer.js instance with play controls\n│\n├── Spectrogram\n│   └── Canvas rendering with frequency range selector\n│\n├── Grid Container (2 columns)\n│   ├── DetectionPanel\n│   │   ├── ConfidenceBar (multiple for different detections)\n│   │   └── Expandable details for method results\n│   │\n│   └── BitPlaneViewer\n│       └── Bit plane bars with bias highlighting\n│\n└── CleanPanel\n    ├── Mode selector dropdown\n    ├── Clean button\n    ├── Save File button (appears after clean)\n    ├── Error display\n    ├── Loading state message\n    └── Results display (when result exists)\n        ├── Stats row (quality loss, time, metadata, patterns)\n        └── DetectionColumn x2 (Before/After)\n            ├── ConfidenceBar (Watermark)\n            ├── ConfidenceBar (AI Watermark)\n            ├── ConfidenceBar (AI Probability)\n            └── Metadata summary\n```\n\n### 5. **API Integration**\n\n**Client API Layer** (`/Users/captain/code/github.com/polez/gui/src/api/client.ts`):\n- `cleanFile(mode)` → POST `/api/clean` - Triggers sanitization\n- `getCleanedWaveform()` → GET `/api/waveform/cleaned` - Shows after waveform\n- `getCleanedAudioUrl()` → Returns `/api/audio/cleaned` for playback\n- `saveCleanedFile()` → POST `/api/save` - Downloads cleaned audio as WAV\n\n**Technology Stack:**\n- React 19.2.0 with TypeScript\n- Tailwind CSS 4.2.1 (utility-first styling)\n- Vite 7.3.1 (build tool)\n- WaveSurfer.js 7.12.1 (waveform visualization)\n- Recharts 3.7.0 (dependency installed but not currently used in UI)\n\n### 6. **Key Design Observations**\n\n- **Dark theme**: All components use zinc/gray palettes with purple accents (`bg-zinc-900`, `text-purple-400`)\n- **Minimal charts**: Despite Recharts dependency, the UI uses custom Canvas rendering (Spectrogram) and simple progress bars (ConfidenceBar) rather than chart libraries\n- **Real-time feedback**: Progress tracking on upload, loading states during operations, error display\n- **Before/after paradigm**: Core UX pattern using side-by-side detection comparisons to show cleaning effectiveness\n- **Mode-based processing**: User can choose cleaning intensity (Fast/Standard/Preserving/Aggressive)\n\nAll source files are located in: `/Users/captain/code/github.com/polez/gui/src/`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a2bf2c76f23c9b044 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 39620\ntool_uses: 16\nduration_ms: 36592</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"25366dd4-3fbf-4b97-9824-3bd39fcc08ab","uuid":"64a9e02f-b103-427e-8c5d-f0c8333dff91","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the gui/ frontend directory in /Users/captain/code/github.com/polez. I need to understand:\n1. The main React components and their structure\n2. How the clean endpoint response is handled/displayed in the frontend\n3. What verification or quality score UI exists (if any)\n4. The overall component hierarchy\n\nFocus on src/ files in the gui/ directory. Be thorough - look at all component files.","agentId":"a2bf2c76f23c9b044","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the frontend structure. Let me compile my findings:\n\n## Frontend Exploration Report: Polez GUI\n\nI've thoroughly explored the `/Users/captain/code/github.com/polez/gui/src` directory. Here's a comprehensive analysis:\n\n### 1. **Main React Compon